{{nihongo|'''Kota Jinja'''|居多神社||}} is the [[Japan]]ese [[Shinto shrine]] in [[ Jyoetsu, Niigata]].<ref>Kotodamaya.com, [http://www.kotodamaya.com/kota-jinja/ "Kota Jinja"]; retrieved 2012-10-24.</ref>

==History==
Kota was one of the chief Shinto shrines (''[[ichinomiya]]'') of the old [[Echigo Province]].  It serves today as one of the ''ichinomiya'' of [[Niigata Prefecture]].<ref>[http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/images/uploads/EOS070712Ab.pdf "Nationwide List of ''Ichinomiya''," p. 2]; retrieved 2012-3-13.</ref>

